                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1357" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL HARRIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am assistant to Thomas and John Deverell, dra<lb></lb>pers, in Oxford-street. On the 9th of Oct. the prisoner came into the shop, and while the young man turned to reach down some goods that she asked for, I saw her take this print and put under her shawl—I let her go to the door, and told the young man to fetch her back—he did so, and this dress was taken from under her shawl, in the shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did you not have any dealings with her? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—she said, "I never intended to steal it."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Who lifted up her shawl? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> The young man, and I took the print from her.</p>
